  monumentInformation:
    monumentInformation:
    - title: Who Built It
      details:
      - The Colosseum was commissioned by Emperor Vespasian of the Flavian dynasty
        in 70-72 CE as a gift to the Roman people.
      - It was completed under Emperor Titus in 80 CE, with later modifications by
        his brother, Emperor Domitian.
    - title: Where It Is Located
      details:
      - The Colosseum is located in the heart of Rome, Italy, just east of the Roman
        Forum.
      - It stands in the Piazza del Colosseo, symbolizing the grandeur of ancient
        Rome.
    - title: When It Was Built
      details:
      - Construction of the Colosseum began in 70-72 CE during the reign of Emperor
        Vespasian.
      - It was completed in 80 CE, taking approximately 8 years to finish. Additional
        improvements were made under Emperor Domitian around 81-96 CE.
    - title: Who Is It Protected By
      details:
      - The Colosseum was designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1980, recognized
        for its historical and cultural importance.
      - It is protected and maintained by the Italian Ministry of Culture and various
        heritage organizations to ensure its preservation.
    - title: Why It Was Built
      details:
      - The Colosseum was built as a massive amphitheater for public spectacles such
        as gladiator combats, animal hunts, and mock naval battles.
      - It served as a symbol of Rome's power, engineering brilliance, and the Flavian
        dynasty's generosity towards the Roman people.
